{
  "texts": [
    "These specialized applications of diffusion-based methods highlight the versatility of generative AI, addressing the need for authenticity in digital art, personalization of visual attributes, scalability in design formats, and transparency in image layers.",
    "As these technologies advance, they promise to reshape the landscape of digital content creation, offering tools that can adapt to an array of specialized tasks while preserving the integrity and quality of the generated materials.Table 3.",
    "Method Categorization by Task.",
    "Task MethodControllable Generation ILVR [28], Textual Inversion [46], ControlNet [171], Uni-ControlNet [179], DreamBooth [119], RPG framework [160], PHDiffusion [94] Content Editing GLIDE [108], Prompt-to-Prompt [55], Custom Diffusion [75], InstructPix2Pix [13], pix2pixzero [111] StylizationInST [175], DiffStyler [64], DreamStyler [1], StyleDrop [130] Quality Enhancement eDiff-I [5], Muse [20], PIXART-𝛼 [22], ScaleCrafter [54] Specialized Tasks ProSpect [174], VectorFusion [65], LayerDiffusion [170], Diffusion Model Originality [131] In Table 3 we summarize the discussed research and provide more examples, to establish correspondence between different generative tasks and methods.",
    "Encoder-decoder: Lu et al. [94] innovate with a dual encoder setup in their PHDiffusion model for painterly image harmonization, which features a lightweight adaptive encoder and a Dual Encoder Fusion (DEF) module, allowing for a more nuanced manipulation of foreground features to blend photographic objects into paintings seamlessly."
